    "body": "Hey guys I tried running the latest release https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/releases/tag/1.8.50 with Prysm in our testnet using this: \r\n```\r\nnethermind --config=/home/nethermind/configs/goerli.cfg --JsonRpc.Enabled=true  --JsonRpc.BufferResponses=true\r\n```\r\nunfortunately I still have some issues to do with unmarshalling `big Ints` in block bodies. \r\nEx: \r\n```\r\nERROR powchain: could not query block with height 2881125: json: cannot unmarshal hex number with leading zero digits into Go struct field rpcBlock.transactions of type *hexutil.Big\r\n```\r\nWe use go-ethereum's json-rpc client library to interface with all eth1 clients. Unmarshalling of responses fail here:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/a981b60c25e6be35ec37cf9b9625017c5fa67fdc/common/hexutil/json.go#L362 \r\n\r\nThe method `eth_getBlockByNumber` only fails whenever we request a specific block instead of the `latest`. Any ideas on how to proceed here ? \r\n",
