    "updated_at": "2020-06-29T16:16:52Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "`EthModule` in `Nethermind.JsonRpc` contains series of methods to access block information. [Prysm Eth2 client](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm) uses these methods to extract data about blocks in order to extract Eth1 deposits of Eth2 validators. In particular we can assume that `eth_getBlockByHash` and `eth_getBlockByNumber` methods are used. Documentation of these methods can be found here: [JSON RPC Wiki](https://eth.wiki/json-rpc/API). Importantly the second parameter of these calls - a `bool` value - defines whether whole transaction objects are retrieved or only hashes. Based on Prysm reporting and after anlyzing their code I assume that the version with `true` value does not return properly formatted data. This should be compare with a synchronized `Goerli` Geth instance.\r\n\r\n1) create a test curl method calling `eth_getBlockByNumber(\"[some block number for a block with transactions]\", true)`\r\n2) synchronize `Goerli` on Geth\r\n3) synchronize `Goerli` on Nethermind\r\n4) verify if the returned data is the same\r\n5) if not the same then fix in Nethermind\r\n6) if same then ensure that the data is same for all `Goerli` blocks\r\n7) if the data is same for all `Goerli` blocks then launch Prysm against the Nethermind node and wait for the error and then issue the request for that particular block and check if it differs from a Geth version for this particular block and report back to Prysm if same (unlikely)",
